<https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/1052> a hpcom:Book,
        hpcom:BookReading,
        hpcom:RenderedItem,
        schema:Book ;
    hpcom:book_id hpcom:1052 ;
    hpcom:book_owned_medium hpcom:PhysicalBook ;
    hpcom:book_read_medium hpcom:PhysicalBook ;
    hpcom:book_status hpcom:book-read ;
    hpcom:date_book_read "2026-06-28T23:59:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:aggregatedRating hptag:Rating4 ;
    schema:author "Rachel Kushner" ;
    schema:dateCreated "2024"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction ;
    schema:name "Creation Lake" ;
    schema:review "The reactions to this book are interesting. It seems that a lot of people picked up this book because it promised to be a 'spy thriller' (misleading marketing?) and it is to do with spying but to call it a thriller is definitely inaccurate. This is a book about society and individuality, masquedering or rather set in a spy setting. The premise is simple. But the writing and elaborations are the highlight. It demanded to be read slowly and carefully to absord the tinest of things, sometimes that came as fully formed, for example observations on the situation. The book also contains a large amount of fictitous correspondence with a crazy guy living in a cave who goes on an on about Neanderthals (as a rejection of who we are today?) Good book, interesting writing."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/1052"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/1053> a hpcom:Book,
