    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction,
        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "Permutation City" ;
    schema:review "Permutation City is the book about multiverses, cyberspaces, and post-AI consciousness - all rolled into a physics and mathematical construct. The sheer scope of imagination here is immense - and that's what makes this a pleasure to read. I like hard sci-fi that also manages to push the boundaries of several things at once - and Greg Egan is an interesting person to read about this. I'm compelled to buy all his books and read through them."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/2"^^xsd:anyURI .

