    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction ;
    schema:name "Hitman Anders and the Meaning of it all" ;
    schema:review "The book starts off at a good spot. There's simple exposition, situational humour, and all the makings of a good recipie. By the end, it got boring, repetitive, the humour had all but become stale and there was nothing special anymore. A nice book if this had been half its length, or had spent some time on its characters instead of shuffling them from scene to scene."@en ;
