    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction,
        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "Harry Potter and the Methods of Rationality" ;
    schema:review "It started off as incredibly clever, and looked to be a fun parody. Instead, it went quickly down a deep dark hole and kept going in. A circle-jerk vehicle for the author's force insertion of their ideas about 'rationality'. Then I looked up the author's other works - found some stuff about AI and safety and alignment -- so more crazy stuff. Makes sense. Didn't like it. DNF."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/895"^^xsd:anyURI .

