    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction ;
    schema:name "Mild Vertigo" ;
    schema:review "This book is a modern character study on the mediocre life of a Japanese housewife. Excellent writing and an amazing way of present the 'wall of text' or 'stream of consciousness' approach where sentences never end and an entire story is told. Nothing spectacular happens - which is how life goes by most of the time."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/911"^^xsd:anyURI .

