        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "H. P. Lovecraft: The Complete Fiction" ;
    schema:review "A classic and a giant in literature, Lovecraft's unique stories led to the use of 'Lovecraftian' as a genre of Eldritch horrors in itself. Good read, though it is difficult to appreciate these fully now that they have had so much influence and imitation and adoption in modern literature. I think I would have liked a lot more details now."@en ;
