    schema:author "Greg Bear" ;
    schema:dateCreated "1999"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction,
        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "Darwin's Radio" ;
    schema:review "Initially, I thought this would be a biological thriller about evolution (as in Darwin), which it is, but the topic is quite surprisingly subtle and well thought out. In the book, there is a mutation that changes the human genetic makeup and wrecks havoc with birth and society. Good, well thought out writing, and fun to read in a scientifically curious way."@en ;
