    hpcom:date_book_read "2025-10-12T00:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:aggregatedRating hptag:Rating3 ;
    schema:author "Kate Crawford" ;
    schema:dateCreated "2015"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookNonFiction ;
    schema:name "Atlas of AI: Power, Politics, and the Planetary Costs of Artificial Intelligence" ;
    schema:review "A recommendation for people looking into AI and its troubles. I think this was a bit too late for me, and in general felt aimed at someone else as I've had far too much exposure to these through my work. Recommended for people who want a more generalist perspective and would benefit from some additional details. The phrasing of 'atlas' really through me off, and I was expecting a more systematic structure and navigation. Instead the work means more about getting a perspective, which I've had from other books."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/995"^^xsd:anyURI .

